RIYADH: The King Salman Humanitarian Aid and Relief Center (KSRelief) has distributed 25.894 tons of food baskets to needy families in Yemenâ€™s Marib governorate on Friday, benefiting 1,624 individuals. This comes within the food assistance project, provided by Saudi Arabia through KSRelief for needy families in Yemen. The KSRelief team also continued distributing various relief aid to those affected by the floods in Pakistan. The KSrelief distributed on Friday 425 food baskets, in the Dera Ghazi Khan district of Punjab province, benefiting 2,972 individuals.